{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"9fb3004c-8088-4eea-8386-f99bed4ad744","content":"**MSTest.Sdk 4.x dropped the VSTest compatibility layer by default.**\n\nIn 3.x, the SDK shipped both the new Microsoft.Testing.Platform runner **and** the VSTest adapter/bridge, so `vstest.console` could still discover tests. Starting with 4.0, only the new platform runner is included.\n\n### Fix options\n\n**Option A — Re-enable the VSTest adapter** (quick CI fix):\n\nAdd this to your `.csproj` / `Directory.Build.props`:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <EnableMicrosoftTestingExtensionsCodeCoverage>false</EnableMicrosoftTestingExtensionsCodeCoverage>\n  <TestingExtensionsProfile>Default</TestingExtensionsProfile>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\nand add the NuGet package:\n\n```\nMSTest.Analyzers → already included\nMSTest.TestAdapter → re-add explicitly\n```\n\n**Option B — Migrate your CI to the new runner** (recommended long-term):\n\nReplace `vstest.console` with:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test          # works if <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n# — or —\ndotnet run --project YourTests.csproj   # runs the built-in test host directly\n```\n\nSet in your project:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\nOption B is the intended path forward — the new platform is faster and supports parallel execution natively.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"87fa94ed-a188-486a-89e3-40afe8457e2e","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about a breaking change between MSTest.Sdk 3.8.0 and 4.1.0 regarding test discovery with vstest.console. This is a known change in the MSTest ecosystem that I can answer from my knowledge.\n\nStarting with MSTest.Sdk 3.x, Microsoft introduced the \"Microsoft.Testing.Platform\" (also known as the new test platform) as an alternative to VSTest. In MSTest.Sdk 3.x, both VSTest and the new testing platform were supported by default.\n\nIn MSTest.Sdk 4.0+, the default changed: the VSTest compatibility layer is no longer included by default. \n\nWith version 4.x, projects only support Microsoft.Testing.Platform out of the box, so running tests through `vstest.console.exe` or the VSTest runner won't discover anything. To fix this, you can either migrate to the new testing platform or restore VSTest support by adding the appropriate configuration flag or bridge package.","outputTokens":804},"id":"755158cb-7a27-4975-881d-049882059f17","timestamp":"2026-04-05T01:08:04.031Z","parentId":"e35ba385-3068-4cd5-a373-e1e3d4a6968e"}
